        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 23 at 3:42PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 342 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 4 miles west of New Mobeetie to 8 miles
southeast of Allison. Movement was northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Canadian, Briscoe, Wheeler, New Mobeetie, Twitty, Allison, Glazier,
Lake Marvin, Kellerville, and Mobeetie.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
